TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Time-Sharing Queue
AU  - Adiri, I.
AU  - Avi-Itzhak, B.
Y1  - 1969/07/01
PY  - 1969
DA  - 1969/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.15.11.639
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.15.11.639
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 639
EP  - 657
VL  - 15
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The paper investigates in detail a single server single queue time-sharing system with homogeneous Poisson arrivals and exponentially distributed service times. The important variables affecting the design and operation of the system were investigated, and the results are given in terms of steady-state expectations and distribution transforms. An attempt is made to demonstrate the influence of various systems's parameters on the overall performance. Special attention is given to optimisation with respect to quantum size. It is hoped that some of the results may serve as guidelines in the design and operation of time-sharing systems.
AB  - The paper investigates in detail a single server single queue time-sharing system with homogeneous Poisson arrivals and exponentially distributed service times. The important variables affecting the design and operation of the system were investigated, and the results are given in terms of steady-state expectations and distribution transforms. An attempt is made to demonstrate the influence of various systems's parameters on the overall performance. Special attention is given to optimisation with respect to quantum size. It is hoped that some of the results may serve as guidelines in the design and operation of time-sharing systems.
